  contentHeader: `Famous Football Club Owners and Their Clubs`,
  content: "<p class='first'>Few will have failed to notice Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenny’s Wrexham making headlines and breaking records in recent weeks. Owning a football is nothing new for celebrities; think Elton John at Watford, Alan Sugar or even Delia Smith at Norwich as just three examples.</p><p>What’s perhaps less well-known are the growing number of celebrities investing in football clubs both in the UK and in the States. Here are some familiar faces who double as football club owners.</p><h3><u>Lebron James: Liverpool FC</u></h3><div><img src='/images/lebron.jpg' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain lg:max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/lebron-james-poses-new-liverpool-26193704'>Liverpool FC</a></p></div><p>LeBron is said to own a 2% stake in the Merseyside club, reportedly investing 4.9 million pounds in 2011. Thanks to the success the club has enjoyed in the subsequent years, this investment looks like a savvy one, his initial investment estimated to have grown to around 24 million.</p><h3><u>Michael B Jordan: Bournemouth FC</u></h3><div><img src='/images/michael-b-jordan.jpg.webp' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain lg:max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.essentiallysports.com/soccer-football-news-black-panther-and-creed-superstar-michael-b-jordan-invests-in-french-soccer-team-alongside-american-billionaire-bill-foley-after-bournemouth-success/'>Essentially Sports</a></p></div><p>Michael B. Jordan, star of films Black Panther and Creed, is a minority stakeholder in the south coast team. Jordan joined a consortium of investors with Bill Foley, an American billionaire, who invested in the team in 2022 following their promotion to the Premier League in 2021. Jordan explained that his presence could help raise the profile of the team, explaining, “I'm just ready to kind of maximise potential, see what I can bring to the table, help bring the popularity of the players in the team up”.</p><h3><u>Mindy Kaling: Swansea FC</u></h3><div><img src='/images/mindy-kaling.jpg.webp' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain lg:max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.thesun.co.uk/sport/football/5163773/us-office-mindy-kaling-hollywood-swansea-owners/'>The Sun</a></p></div><p>Who would think that The Office star and writer Mindy Kaling would be interested in football? Mindy owns a 1% stake in the Welsh club, explaining to Oprah Winfrey that an investment in football is “a smart choice”.</p><h3><u>Natalie Portman: Angel City</u></h3><div><img src='/images/natalie-portman.jpg' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain h-[210px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffconway/2020/11/12/meet-the-angel-city-football-club-and-the-trailblazing-women-that-built-it/?sh=74df8360279c'>Forbes</a></p></div><p>Not only did Natalie Portman invest in women’s football team Angel City, she actually founded it. Other investors in the team include Uzo Aduba (far left) America Ferrera, Christina Aguilera, Jessica Chastain (far right), Jennifer Garner, Eva Longoria (centre) and Serena Williams. Portman and friends are the only celebs on this list to invest in women’s football, seeing a stake in the LA team not only as a wise investment but a chance to raise the profile of the sport and celebrate its athletes.</p><h3><u>Will Ferrell: LAFC</u></h3><div><img src='/images/will-ferrell.webp' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain lg:max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/lafcs-will-ferrell-shows-why-hes-coolest-owner-sports-team-podcast'>Major League Soccer</a></p></div><p>Though most would associate Will Ferrell with ice skating, not football, Ferrell is an investor and supporter of LAFC. Ferrell, apart from being part-owner, is also a huge fan of the team and has been filmed wildly celebrating their victories and even taking part in training sessions with the team.</p><h3><u>Eva Longoria, Kate Upton and Mesut Ozil: Necaxa (Mexico)</u></h3><div><img src='/images/necaxa.jpg.webp' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain lg:max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://www.thescottishsun.co.uk/sport/football/6961046/mesut-ozil-arsena-longoria-upton-necaxa/'>The Scottish Sun</a></p></div><p>Former Real Madrid and Arsenal star Mesut Ozil, actress Eva Longoria and model Kate Upton joined a group of investors which took a 50% share in Mexican first division side Necaxa, bottom of LigaMX at the time of investment in 2021. The Mexican league is not only hugely popular in Mexico but also in the States due to the many fans of Mexican descent in the country.</p><h3><u>Reese Witherspoon: Nashville FC</u></h3><div><img src='/images/reese-witherspoon.jpg' class='block m-auto  md:pt-5 object-contain max-w-[450px]' /><p class='text-center text-sm py-1 max-w-[600px] m-auto'>Image source:<a href='https://people.com/parents/reese-witherspoon-husband-jim-toth-sons-root-for-tennessee-titans/'>People</a></p></div><p>Reese Witherspoon and now ex-husband Jim Toth became minority owners of Nashville FC in 2022. A Nashville native herself, Witherspoon described herself as “thrilled” to join the enterprise. Witherspoon has been photographed several times with her family cheering on the team.</p><p>With the number of American owners now reaching eight out of the twenty Premier League teams, we can surely expect more famous faces in the stands in the coming seasons.</p>",
